1
00:00:00,640 --> 00:00:05,240
Mom, I've been thinking,
and I feel really bad.

2
00:00:05,940 --> 00:00:09,250
I was so busy running around
with Baek Ho with the flyers we made...

3
00:00:09,250 --> 00:00:10,750
to find Grandfather's daughter...

4
00:00:11,180 --> 00:00:14,450
that I completely neglected
searching for your parents.

5
00:00:14,750 --> 00:00:15,990
And I'm your daughter.

6
00:00:17,590 --> 00:00:19,390
Sweetie, is that how you feel?

7
00:00:19,920 --> 00:00:22,830
So you're going to make flyers for me?

8
00:00:22,890 --> 00:00:27,300
Yes. To start, tell me everything you know
about your parents.

9
00:00:27,670 --> 00:00:30,700
And tell me when you started living
at the orphanage.

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,300
It's okay, you don't have to.

11
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,540
Even if you make flyers,

12
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:38,040
I don't even know
if my parents are still alive.

13
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:40,980
They would be very old by now.

14
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:45,080
Besides, I'm not getting my hopes up.

15
00:00:45,380 --> 00:00:49,450
But what if you have siblings
or relatives?

16
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:51,560
They might even be looking for you.

17
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:54,130
You think so?

18
00:00:54,860 --> 00:00:57,530
For starters,
just tell me which orphanage it was.

19
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,900
I can start looking for information there.

20
00:01:01,230 --> 00:01:03,540
The Sohan Orphanage in Incheon.

21
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:07,940
The director there gave me
the name Park Young Mi.

22
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,610
Sohan Orphanage...

23
00:01:09,610 --> 00:01:10,610
Park Young Mi.

24
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:12,940
- And then?
- After that,

25
00:01:13,340 --> 00:01:15,580
I was sent to an orphanage in Pyeongtaek.

26
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:20,720
- That necklace.
- The necklace?

27
00:01:22,050 --> 00:01:25,660
You mean the one
Chae Hwa Young accused you of stealing?

28
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:29,090
Actually, that necklace isn't mine.

29
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:32,930
What? The necklace from Dad's things
isn't yours?

30
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:36,000
No, that one is my real necklace.

31
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:39,070
You know the one we found
on the shop floor later?

32
00:01:39,370 --> 00:01:40,740
That one's the fake.

33
00:01:41,010 --> 00:01:43,780
It's not the one I was wearing
in the first place.

34
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:45,240
Really?

35
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:46,580
Really?

36
00:01:46,850 --> 00:01:48,850
So your mother lost the real one?

37
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:52,750
Yes. As her memories started coming back,
she realized...

38
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:54,390
it wasn't a gift from my dad,

39
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:57,560
but one she's had since the orphanage.

40
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:00,060
The one she's wearing now is similar,

41
00:02:00,530 --> 00:02:02,430
but at some point
it was swapped with a fake.

42
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:05,130
Wait, so that necklace must be...

43
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:07,870
a huge clue to finding her parents.

44
00:02:07,930 --> 00:02:11,270
Exactly. She said the word "Chang"
was clearly engraved on it.

45
00:02:12,070 --> 00:02:13,200
Wait, that's weird.

46
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:15,840
That means someone stole
the real necklace...

47
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:18,880
and left a similar-looking fake one
in its place.

48
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:20,450
That's what you're thinking too, right?

49
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:25,020
But what could the person who stole it
possibly want with it?

50
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:26,350
That's the real question.

51
00:02:26,890 --> 00:02:29,690
A while ago, my mom was wearing
that fake necklace...

52
00:02:29,690 --> 00:02:31,620
while she was working
at Grandfather's house.

53
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,360
What?

54
00:02:33,630 --> 00:02:34,690
My necklace!

55
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,430
- Mom!
- What are you doing?

56
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:42,230
- That hurts!
- What do you think you're doing?

57
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,440
This woman stole my necklace!

58
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:49,010
That's when Chae Hwa Young threw a fit,
saying it was her necklace.

59
00:02:49,070 --> 00:02:52,010
Wait, so you're saying Chae Hwa Young
had the exact same necklace?

60
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:55,180
She must have had a similar one.

61
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:57,920
That's probably why she made such a scene
about it being stolen.

62
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:59,180
Something's not right.

63
00:02:59,450 --> 00:03:00,850
What if that necklace...

64
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:03,120
is actually an incredible clue?

65
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:05,160
Let's say...

66
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,060
And this is just a hypothetical.

67
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:11,760
If Chae Hwa Young stole the real necklace
and replaced it with a fake,

68
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:15,130
what could she have been planning
to do with it?

69
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:21,110
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

70
00:03:21,170 --> 00:03:23,210
Go and wipe all the CCTV footage.

71
00:03:23,510 --> 00:03:26,740
It'll be a disaster if I'm on the footage
at the hospital with Seo Rin.

72
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:28,510
- You need to hurry.
- Yes, ma'am.

73
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:31,320
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

74
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:35,150
Kang Baek Ho. Oh Jang Mi.

75
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:38,560
You think you can trap me
with a pathetic little parking receipt?

76
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,090
Not a chance.

77
00:03:42,990 --> 00:03:45,600
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

78
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:47,500
Is something wrong?

79
00:03:48,730 --> 00:03:50,070
Oh Jang Mi and Kang Baek Ho...

80
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,070
have my parking stub
from the hospital where Seo Rin died,

81
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,370
and they're threatening me with it.

82
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:57,540
Those two are driving me insane.

83
00:03:57,980 --> 00:04:00,680
Something as flimsy as a parking receipt
can't prove anything.

84
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:04,720
What if my face shows up
on a nearby CCTV, even for a second?

85
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:07,550
Those two vipers are searching
frantically right now,

86
00:04:07,890 --> 00:04:10,690
dead-set on digging up every bit
of CCTV footage in Ohjeong.

87
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:13,060
Then why would you do
something so awful...

88
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:15,490
if you were going to be this nervous?

89
00:04:15,790 --> 00:04:17,630
Why'd you do it in the first place?

90
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:19,460
Do you think I meant to kill Seo Rin?

91
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:23,330
Do you think I'm some psychopath
who thinks nothing of killing someone?

92
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,970
I had my reasons for doing it.

93
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:28,740
- A reason for killing someone?
- Enough.

94
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:34,380
Do you think I wanted to kill Seo Rin,
the girl I raised as my own for 30 years?

95
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:38,680
It tore me apart to do it.
But I had no choice.

96
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,490
Then tell me why you had no other choice
but to kill her.

97
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:44,290
It was Jung Suk Hee.

98
00:04:44,290 --> 00:04:45,990
That half-wit, Jung Suk Hee,

99
00:04:46,490 --> 00:04:48,790
was Chairman Ma's real daughter,
who we all thought was dead.

100
00:04:49,090 --> 00:04:50,730
And Seo Rin found out.

101
00:04:51,660 --> 00:04:52,830
Jang Mi's mother is...

102
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,400
Chairman Ma's biological daughter?

103
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,500
That's right.

104
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:01,110
Seo Rin threw a fit, saying she was going
to tell Chairman Ma everything.

105
00:05:01,110 --> 00:05:02,940
I had no choice!

106
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:09,050
Just imagine if Chairman Ma found out.

107
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:12,520
The life I built for 30 years
would be over.

108
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,750
You think I'd be the only one to go down?

109
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:16,190
You'd be finished too! All of us!

110
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:26,430
Looks like Manager Lee is
on his way to Ohjeong.

111
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:29,800
I guess our little trap
with the parking receipt worked.

112
00:05:29,970 --> 00:05:33,200
He must be on his way
to destroy any CCTV footage...

113
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,810
of Chae Hwa Young in the Ohjeong area.

114
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:36,010
Just like you said, Baek Ho,

115
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:38,080
Chae Hwa Young completely took the bait.

116
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:42,250
We just have to follow Manager Lee
and catch him destroying the evidence.

117
00:05:42,710 --> 00:05:43,720
Right.

118
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,790
Yes, ma'am.
I was just about to head out...

119
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:53,730
No. Don't go to Ohjeong.

120
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:56,130
What? What do you mean...

121
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:57,300
Think about it.

122
00:05:57,430 --> 00:06:00,670
If all this fuss is over just one receipt,

123
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:03,100
it means they don't have
any actual footage of me.

124
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:05,340
If they had any incriminating footage,

125
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:09,010
they would've gone straight to the police
instead of coming here to threaten me.

126
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:11,510
Those sly foxes were just baiting us,

127
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:15,680
hoping we would lead them
right to the evidence ourselves.

128
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:18,220
That makes sense.

129
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:22,020
I'm sure they're staked out
in the parking garage somewhere,

130
00:06:22,850 --> 00:06:24,690
waiting to follow you
the second you make a move.

131
00:06:26,020 --> 00:06:28,660
We would have been in real trouble
if Jun Ho hadn't warned me.

132
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:32,000
Understood.
I'll head back to the office right away.

133
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,780
What? Manager Lee is just leaving.

134
00:06:47,450 --> 00:06:51,080
I think they figured out
we were baiting them.

135
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:53,920
Darn it. We were so close.

136
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,920
The nerve of them.

137
00:07:01,030 --> 00:07:02,790
- What?
- Hwa Young.

138
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:05,700
I heard you were back in the CEO chair.

139
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,570
Congratulations.

140
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:09,470
Nam Bong.

141
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:11,600
How did you know?

142
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:15,810
- Please.
- Thanks.

143
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:21,550
Do you think there's anything
about you I don't know?

144
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:25,920
These flowers smell wonderful.

145
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:30,450
That was a close call...

146
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:37,430
Manager Lee.
Take better care of my Hwa Young.

147
00:07:37,530 --> 00:07:41,230
When she became CEO,
you should have reported to me first.

148
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:42,570
What kind of assistant are you?

149
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:45,840
- That's negligence, plain and simple.
- What?

150
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:46,940
Isn't that right, Hwa Young?

151
00:07:48,770 --> 00:07:53,510
And bring a vase for these flowers,
and get some tea for Hwa Young and me.

152
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,950
I heard you moved out.

153
00:07:57,650 --> 00:07:59,180
I was actually wondering about that.

154
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:11,700
Maybe I should've made flyers too.

155
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:16,470
My parents are getting older,
so I really need to find them soon.

156
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:19,340
If I put a picture...

157
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:21,010
of the four-leaf clover embroidery
on the flyer...

158
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,240
The four-leaf clover bracelet.

159
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:29,510
This is my four-leaf clover bracelet.

160
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:32,250
I found it in that other grandma's room.

161
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,590
Give it here.

162
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:39,760
What?

163
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:43,730
This is the newborn baby jacket...

164
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:45,630
I got for Seo Rin.

165
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:47,160
My necklace!

166
00:08:49,370 --> 00:08:50,370
What are you doing?

167
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:02,580
Why is Chae Hwa Young claiming
my necklace is hers?

168
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:05,620
And why was she hiding...

169
00:09:06,020 --> 00:09:09,450
the four-leaf clover bracelet
and Seo Rin's newborn clothes?

170
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:12,560
Those are all the things
my parents would recognize me by.

171
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:16,130
Don't tell me Chae Hwa Young...

172
00:09:17,190 --> 00:09:20,030
knows who my parents are.

173
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,570
No, but then why...

174
00:09:23,570 --> 00:09:26,970
is she trying to stop me
from meeting my parents?

175
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:34,080
From this moment on,

176
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:36,880
if you lie about a single thing,

177
00:09:37,450 --> 00:09:39,050
I won't let you get away with it.

178
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:43,450
Tell me everything you told CEO Chae.

179
00:09:44,590 --> 00:09:45,890
Yes, Chairman.

180
00:09:46,790 --> 00:09:49,930
After her college entrance exams,

181
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:54,570
Young Mi suffered something terrible,
and she tried to kill herself.

182
00:09:55,370 --> 00:09:59,070
But her best friend
and a man named Bok Gil...

183
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:01,440
whom she'd known since childhood,
took care of her.

184
00:10:02,170 --> 00:10:03,410
And that's how she barely survived.

185
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:04,840
Bok Gil?

186
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:07,450
- Oh Bok Gil?
- Yes.

187
00:10:07,950 --> 00:10:10,780
Rumors said they were living together.

188
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:15,790
So how did that Park Young Mi
become Jung Suk Hee?

189
00:10:25,730 --> 00:10:28,570
- Congrats again. Keep in touch.
- I will.

190
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:42,210
What does she want now?
As if I'm on her level.

191
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:43,550
What a waste of time.

192
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:46,580
- What is it?
- Hwa Young,

193
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:49,620
I was going back and forth on what to do,

194
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:52,890
but I figured I owed it to you to call.

195
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:56,660
Don't make me laugh.
What's this talk about owing me?

196
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,300
Just spit it out. I'm busy.

197
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:03,870
You know that woman who showed up before,
pretending to be the Chairman's daughter?

198
00:11:04,070 --> 00:11:05,600
- Park Young Mi?
- Yes!

199
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:08,810
She's with the Chairman right now.

200
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:10,010
What?

201
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:13,240
- Why is she meeting with Father?
- How would I know?

202
00:11:13,310 --> 00:11:15,950
What have you been doing this whole time
and not trying to find out?

203
00:11:16,150 --> 00:11:18,320
You need to hurry up and find out
what they're talking about!

204
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,080
Gosh, she's so loud.

205
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:22,890
I give her a hot tip,
and this is the thanks I get.

206
00:11:23,890 --> 00:11:28,160
I mean, how am I supposed to listen
when Secretary Kim is guarding the study?

207
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:30,030
Just figure it out, okay?

208
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:31,800
That's an order. Understood?

209
00:11:31,930 --> 00:11:33,330
You brat! Who do you think I am?

210
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:35,330
I'm hanging up! Darn it.

211
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:37,870
Seriously, that old man...

212
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:40,370
I can't let my guard down
for a single second.

213
00:11:40,870 --> 00:11:42,470
Why did he call in the fake Park Young Mi?

214
00:11:42,470 --> 00:11:43,910
What's he trying to find out?

215
00:11:44,540 --> 00:11:45,610
I have to do something.

216
00:11:46,380 --> 00:11:48,510
At this rate, everything I've worked for
will be ruined.

217
00:11:57,420 --> 00:12:01,660
Goodness, these sales numbers
just keep dropping.

218
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:04,730
This is a real problem.

219
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:08,670
You.

220
00:12:09,630 --> 00:12:11,000
What are you doing here at this hour?

221
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,340
It's just...

222
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,540
I heard that woman, the fake daughter,
came to see you.

223
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:17,840
I was worried she was bothering you again.

224
00:12:18,610 --> 00:12:20,580
You've got to be kidding me.

225
00:12:20,850 --> 00:12:24,980
Why do you tell her every little thing?
She's busy enough as it is.

226
00:12:24,980 --> 00:12:27,220
No, I just wanted to ask CEO Chae...

227
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:30,320
what she thought we should do
if that woman pulled any more stunts.

228
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:32,720
That's all I was asking.

229
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:36,430
She did ask for some money.

230
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:37,560
Money?

231
00:12:38,060 --> 00:12:39,060
Why?

232
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:42,500
What information did she try
to fool you with?

233
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,700
Now that I've found you,
what other information could I need?

234
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:48,270
That's not what I mean.

235
00:12:48,540 --> 00:12:51,380
It seems her child is very sick.

236
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:53,640
I figured she must be desperate to see me.

237
00:12:53,910 --> 00:12:55,710
So I gave her some money
and sent her on her way.

238
00:12:56,180 --> 00:12:59,280
I warned her not to come back,
so she won't.

239
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:03,290
Why get so worked up over nothing
and come rushing over here?

240
00:13:23,070 --> 00:13:25,710
The number you have dialed
is not in service.

241
00:13:26,110 --> 00:13:27,440
Please check the number...

242
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:30,920
That fake Park Young Mi
already changed her number.

243
00:13:31,780 --> 00:13:33,520
Did she really just come for the money?

244
00:13:34,650 --> 00:13:36,620
If that were the case,
she would've tried to blackmail me.

245
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:41,830
What could she have said?
I have no way of knowing!

246
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,900
Manager Lee,
I need you to look into that woman.

247
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:54,240
That fake Park Young Mi!

248
00:13:54,940 --> 00:13:57,910
You've hidden
the fake Park Young Mi away, right?

249
00:13:58,110 --> 00:14:01,450
Yes, sir.
CEO Chae will never be able to find her.

250
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:03,450
Through a reliable channel,

251
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:05,180
I'm arranging for her to settle
somewhere out of town.

252
00:14:05,350 --> 00:14:08,520
And what's the status
on Jung Suk Hee's DNA test?

253
00:14:08,590 --> 00:14:11,560
I'm still trying to get a sample.
It's taking longer than expected.

254
00:14:11,690 --> 00:14:14,360
Then when Jung Suk Hee comes to our house,

255
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:16,190
find a way to collect a sample discreetly.

256
00:14:16,630 --> 00:14:19,900
And bring me the results
as soon as you possibly can.

257
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:21,570
Yes, sir.

258
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:23,030
This matter...

259
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:27,670
must not reach Chae Hwa Young's ears.
Got it?

260
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:31,140
Chae Hwa Young showing up here
pretending to be Eun Hye...

261
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:32,940
is largely your fault.

262
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,680
I'm sorry, Chairman.

263
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:37,780
No.

264
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:39,720
It seems to me...

265
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:43,490
that Chae Hwa Young's people
might be watching you.

266
00:14:45,290 --> 00:14:47,990
This isn't going to work.
We need to find another way.

267
00:14:49,660 --> 00:14:51,560
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

268
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,930
How could the fake Park Young Mi
just disappear like that?

269
00:14:56,600 --> 00:15:00,100
She changed her number,
and she was gone from her address.

270
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:01,910
I have a bad feeling about this.

271
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:04,170
Something's going on here.

272
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:07,950
Maybe she committed some kind
of financial crime, like gambling,

273
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:10,580
and just disappeared after
extorting money from Chairman Ma?

274
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:11,980
The problem is...

275
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:15,520
that I'm worried that witch got excited
about the money...

276
00:15:15,950 --> 00:15:18,960
and spilled everything she told me
to Chairman Ma.

277
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:21,730
If that were the case, there's no way
Chairman Ma would be this quiet about it.

278
00:15:22,030 --> 00:15:25,500
No. You never know
what that sly old fox, Chairman Ma,

279
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:28,430
is planning behind my back.

280
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:30,470
Even so,
he won't be able to find anything.

281
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:33,100
We fabricated and deleted everything.

282
00:15:34,710 --> 00:15:38,210
Anyway, keep an eye on Secretary Kim.
Call me the second anything happens.

283
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:39,740
Right.

284
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:46,550
What a headache.
I can never catch a break.

285
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:50,520
I became Chairman Ma's daughter.
Shouldn't I have the world at my feet?

286
00:15:50,890 --> 00:15:54,430
So why does every day have to feel
like I'm walking on eggshells?

287
00:16:02,130 --> 00:16:03,970
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

288
00:16:09,170 --> 00:16:10,170
Jun Ho.

289
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:12,740
Have you cooled down a bit?

290
00:16:15,610 --> 00:16:17,550
You're very disappointed in me,
aren't you?

291
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:18,950
What else is new?

292
00:16:20,950 --> 00:16:22,990
Do you think I'm capable
of being any more disappointed?

293
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:24,920
Don't be like that, Jun Ho.

294
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:28,730
About the majority shareholder,
Choi Ha Joon...

295
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:30,160
Jun Ho.

296
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:33,560
I already have a splitting headache
from work.

297
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:35,830
Why bring up that phantom shareholder?

298
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:38,540
I think Team Leader Jin knows
who Choi Ha Joon really is.

299
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:39,940
Or rather,

300
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,840
at least she seems to have
some information about him.

301
00:16:43,310 --> 00:16:44,480
Team Leader Jin?

302
00:16:45,210 --> 00:16:46,540
She has information on Choi Ha Joon?

303
00:16:47,380 --> 00:16:50,910
Mom, how's our project to make Baek Ho
your son-in-law coming along?

304
00:16:51,850 --> 00:16:55,450
With all this drama from Hwa Young,
I've been so distracted.

305
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:57,990
- I haven't given it a single thought.
- What about CEO Chae?

306
00:16:58,060 --> 00:17:02,130
That fake daughter of the Chairman,
Park Young Mi, or whatever her name is.

307
00:17:02,260 --> 00:17:03,630
She stopped by earlier.

308
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:07,300
When Hwa Young found out,
she threw a huge fit and stormed out.

309
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:11,500
- Really? Park Young Mi?
- Anyway, my sweet Hong Ju.

310
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:16,370
You just focus on
completely seducing Baek Ho...

311
00:17:16,610 --> 00:17:18,610
and figuring out how to get him into bed.

312
00:17:18,940 --> 00:17:21,880
Mom, aren't you jumping the gun?

313
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:25,380
Baek Ho won't give me the time of day,
so what am I supposed to do?

314
00:17:25,450 --> 00:17:26,820
Goodness.

315
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:29,550
Then, is our project to make
the largest shareholder,

316
00:17:29,550 --> 00:17:32,920
Kang Baek Ho,
my son-in-law dead in the water now?

317
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,390
Of course not.

318
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:35,990
I don't know.

319
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:40,360
But why did CEO Chae flip out
when she heard about Park Young Mi?

320
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:41,730
Mom, do you know something?

321
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:43,100
Park Young Mi?

322
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,540
The Sohan Orphanage in Incheon.

323
00:17:45,970 --> 00:17:49,940
The director there gave me
the name Park Young Mi.

324
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:53,510
Anyway, think about it, Mom.
I've got to go.

325
00:17:55,610 --> 00:17:58,550
I overheard you on my way in.
Who's Park Young Mi?

326
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:03,250
- What?
- What did you say about Park Young Mi?

327
00:18:04,460 --> 00:18:06,390
And why should I have to tell you that,
Director Ma?

328
00:18:08,690 --> 00:18:11,230
Jin Hong Ju. Who do you think you are?

329
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:13,100
What gives you the right to be so cocky?

330
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:14,770
Unbelievable.

331
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:17,600
I guess you're taking after CEO Chae,
Director Ma.

332
00:18:17,730 --> 00:18:19,740
That's better.
You should've been polite from the start.

333
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,240
Talk.

334
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:24,440
You said CEO Chae freaked out
when she heard about Park Young Mi?

335
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:29,180
Not the real Park Young Mi.
It was the fake Park Young Mi.

336
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,080
Is that so?

337
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:51,000
- Hong Ju.
- Mrs. Han.

338
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:55,870
I've been feeling so down lately,
so I was hoping we could go shopping.

339
00:18:56,170 --> 00:18:58,040
When would be a good time for you?

340
00:18:58,310 --> 00:19:01,110
Hong Ju. Please, stop doing this.

341
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:03,150
To be honest, this makes me uncomfortable.

342
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:07,990
You know Baek Ho and Jang Mi wed secretly,
don't you?

343
00:19:08,450 --> 00:19:12,890
I'm so hurt. It's not even about Baek Ho.

344
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:17,760
I wanted to go shopping
and have nice meals like we used to.

345
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:20,560
I just wanted to be
like a daughter to you.

346
00:19:22,170 --> 00:19:23,870
Goodness. That's not true.

347
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,770
It's all because
you have feelings for my Baek Ho.

348
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:29,410
I know that's the only reason
you approached me.

349
00:19:29,910 --> 00:19:31,980
Anyway, take care.

350
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:39,850
Back when Oh Jang Mi wasn't
Chairman Ma's biological granddaughter,

351
00:19:40,020 --> 00:19:42,450
she couldn't stand her,
calling her a girl from a side-dish shop.

352
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:44,290
But now, I guess she just adores her.

353
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:49,060
Let's be honest.
All mothers are like that.

354
00:19:49,430 --> 00:19:50,860
To put it bluntly,

355
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:52,460
if my son had to choose...

356
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:56,330
between a girl working at a side-dish shop
and a rich heiress,

357
00:19:56,430 --> 00:19:59,270
every mother in the world
would choose the heiress.

358
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:01,240
That's just human nature.

359
00:20:01,740 --> 00:20:03,510
I don't see anything wrong with that.

360
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:06,580
Mom, are you talking about yourself now?

361
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:08,850
What?

362
00:20:12,820 --> 00:20:15,820
What could Chairman Ma have talked about
with the fake Park Young Mi?

363
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:18,290
This is making me so anxious.

364
00:20:20,390 --> 00:20:21,760
Come on.

365
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:25,430
You called Baek Ho a rootless adoptee
and shuddered at the thought of him.

366
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:28,300
Now that you know he's Choi Ha Joon,
the largest shareholder of Dream Group,

367
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:30,430
look how desperate you are
to make him your son-in-law.

368
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:33,770
This is all for you!

369
00:20:33,770 --> 00:20:37,140
Who knew Kang Baek Ho
was Dream Group's largest shareholder?

370
00:20:37,410 --> 00:20:42,050
The day you marry him,
you'll be rolling in money, you fool.

371
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:45,720
And for once,
I get to enjoy the perks of a son-in-law.

372
00:20:50,490 --> 00:20:51,560
What was that?

373
00:20:52,420 --> 00:20:53,990
What on earth are you saying?

374
00:20:54,190 --> 00:20:55,730
Gosh, darn it.

375
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:57,160
Kang Baek Ho is Choi Ha Joon?

376
00:20:58,030 --> 00:21:00,360
Are you saying Kang Baek Ho
is the largest shareholder, Choi Ha Joon?

377
00:21:00,630 --> 00:21:01,630
Is that it?

378
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:04,800
Oh my.

379
00:21:09,410 --> 00:21:10,410
Mom.

380
00:21:10,870 --> 00:21:14,910
You said the director at the orphanage
named you Park Young Mi, right?

381
00:21:15,580 --> 00:21:16,580
Yes.

382
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:19,450
- Why do you ask?
- Chairman Ma met...

383
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:21,250
the fake Park Young Mi today,

384
00:21:21,590 --> 00:21:23,190
and apparently,
Chae Hwa Young caused a huge scene.

385
00:21:23,450 --> 00:21:25,160
What do you mean, a fake Park Young Mi?

386
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:30,330
How did Park Young Mi become Jung Suk Hee?

387
00:21:30,760 --> 00:21:35,670
Young Mi was a great student.
She could've gotten into Seoul University.

388
00:21:36,070 --> 00:21:39,570
But she was so poor,
she couldn't even dream of college.

389
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:47,110
But then Mr. Jung appeared
and offered to pay for her college.

390
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:49,880
On the condition that
he gets to adopt her.

391
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:52,150
- Adopt her?
- Yes.

392
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:55,490
Right after she was adopted,
she had to take on the family's surname,

393
00:21:55,690 --> 00:21:57,850
and her first name was changed to Suk Hee.

394
00:21:58,420 --> 00:22:01,060
Apparently,
they made her focus only on her studies.

395
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:05,460
The other orphanage kids were so jealous.
They all said her luck had finally turned.

396
00:22:05,860 --> 00:22:06,860
Is that so?

397
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:10,170
I thought she was all alone in this world.

398
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:11,230
But...

399
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:13,740
as it turned out,

400
00:22:15,210 --> 00:22:17,940
he only took Young Mi in so she could
take an exam for someone else.

401
00:22:18,010 --> 00:22:19,010
Take an exam for somebody else?

402
00:22:19,180 --> 00:22:23,250
He wanted her to take the college exam
in place of his own dim-witted daughter.

403
00:22:23,350 --> 00:22:24,350
What?

404
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:26,480
When Young Mi later found out the truth...

405
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:29,090
and threatened to go
to the police in tears,

406
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:30,450
that monster, Mr. Jung,

407
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:34,090
threatened that if she reported him,
she'd be charged as an accomplice too.

408
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,790
So what happened with college?

409
00:22:36,030 --> 00:22:37,230
Forget college.

410
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:40,830
I heard he cut her off
without a penny to her name.

411
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:45,870
How could anyone do that to a poor orphan
with no one to turn to?

412
00:22:46,070 --> 00:22:47,670
It's what an animal would do!

413
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:51,610
After Mr. Jung disowned her,

414
00:22:51,780 --> 00:22:56,010
she found her legal name was Jung Suk Hee
and was devastated, wanting to die.

415
00:22:56,250 --> 00:23:01,790
So you're saying
CEO Chae knows this whole story?

416
00:23:01,990 --> 00:23:02,990
Yes.

417
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:06,690
That evil witch, Chae Hwa Young...

418
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:12,760
She fabricated this entire story
and came to me.

419
00:23:14,430 --> 00:23:17,130
She caused my daughter so much pain.

420
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:20,270
As if stealing Suk Hee's daughter
wasn't bad enough,

421
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,840
she's pulling another stunt like this?

422
00:23:23,340 --> 00:23:25,340
I'll make Chae Hwa Young pay!

423
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:31,280
Based on all the evidence,

424
00:23:31,620 --> 00:23:35,020
it's certain that Chae Hwa Young knows
about the Chairman's biological daughter.

425
00:23:35,290 --> 00:23:37,590
Right? I feel the same way.

426
00:23:37,650 --> 00:23:41,260
She stole your necklace
and the four-leaf clover bracelet.

427
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:44,390
And you saw Seo Rin's newborn clothes
in Chae Hwa Young's drawer, right?

428
00:23:44,660 --> 00:23:48,830
Yes. When I was abandoned
at the orphanage,

429
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:50,300
the necklace was around my neck.

430
00:23:50,430 --> 00:23:51,770
As for the four-leaf clover...

431
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:57,370
- Mom, what is it?
- What's wrong?

432
00:23:57,510 --> 00:23:59,040
Do you remember something?

433
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:06,020
A small four-leaf clover was embroidered
on my own newborn clothes.

434
00:24:06,650 --> 00:24:09,420
But I lost them
when I was adopted by Mr. Jung.

435
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:14,160
That's why when you and Seo Rin were born,

436
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:19,100
I stitched a clover on your baby clothes,
just like mine.

437
00:24:20,030 --> 00:24:23,700
Hoping my girls would always be blessed
with good fortune.

438
00:24:24,030 --> 00:24:25,240
Newborn clothes?

439
00:24:29,740 --> 00:24:30,740
Wait...

440
00:24:31,270 --> 00:24:32,740
No...

441
00:24:32,740 --> 00:24:34,610
It couldn't be, could it, Baek Ho?

442
00:24:34,810 --> 00:24:36,880
It's okay. Try to stay calm.

443
00:24:37,910 --> 00:24:39,820
Mom, you can't be...

444
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:44,550
Baek Ho, do you have the photo
you used for the flyer?

445
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:47,260
Or a picture of the Chairman's family...

446
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:49,630
I have a picture of the Chairman's family.

447
00:24:52,230 --> 00:24:53,230
Here it is.

448
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:12,520
Mom...

449
00:25:13,550 --> 00:25:14,550
I'm...

450
00:25:15,820 --> 00:25:17,490
I'm the Chairman's daughter.

451
00:25:18,660 --> 00:25:19,660
Mom.

452
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:23,860
Then what does that mean for you and Dad?

453
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:25,600
I can't believe it.

454
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:29,170
Dong Seok was adopted.

455
00:25:29,730 --> 00:25:34,000
- What?
- Long ago, before we got married,

456
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:38,210
he told me that he was adopted.

457
00:25:39,310 --> 00:25:40,610
Thank goodness.

458
00:25:42,450 --> 00:25:45,450
But still, I just can't believe it.

459
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:49,650
To think that I'm the Chairman's daughter.

460
00:25:51,590 --> 00:25:54,560
(Genosphere)

461
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:08,910
- Hey.
- Chairman.

462
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:16,510
(DNA Paternity Test Results)

463
00:26:18,850 --> 00:26:22,420
"Test subject Ma Dae Chang..."

464
00:26:24,350 --> 00:26:29,960
"is very likely the biological father
of test subject Jung Suk Hee..."

465
00:26:30,860 --> 00:26:37,500
"with a genetic probability
of 99.99 percent or higher."

466
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,700
"The two individuals..."

467
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:44,610
"are hereby confirmed..."

468
00:26:45,410 --> 00:26:47,880
"as biological parent and child."

469
00:26:52,350 --> 00:26:53,550
Jung Suk Hee...

470
00:26:55,020 --> 00:26:59,020
Jung Suk Hee is Eun Hye.

471
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:06,360
After everything Suk Hee has endured...

472
00:27:07,430 --> 00:27:11,330
She's my own flesh and blood.

473
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:14,240
Goodness...

474
00:27:17,270 --> 00:27:18,380
Goodness...

475
00:27:40,900 --> 00:27:41,900
Goodness...

476
00:27:42,670 --> 00:27:43,770
Eun Hye!

477
00:27:44,430 --> 00:27:45,940
My dear girl.

478
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:50,540
Father!

479
00:27:53,510 --> 00:27:55,880
Yes, my Eun Hye.

480
00:27:57,210 --> 00:28:00,120
It's me. I'm your father.

481
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:05,120
- It's your father, Eun Hye.
- Father.

482
00:28:33,550 --> 00:28:35,150
(The First Man)

483
00:28:35,290 --> 00:28:37,150
That evil witch Chae Hwa Young.

484
00:28:37,650 --> 00:28:41,160
Letting her rot in prison
with three meals a day is not enough.

485
00:28:41,290 --> 00:28:43,490
How do you plan on punishing her?

486
00:28:43,890 --> 00:28:48,770
You're my daughter, so isn't it time
I hand everything over to you?

487
00:28:48,930 --> 00:28:51,000
I'm finally going to be the head of Dream.

488
00:28:51,430 --> 00:28:53,940
I have something urgent
to discuss with you,

489
00:28:54,540 --> 00:28:55,940
so come to my study now.

490
00:28:55,940 --> 00:28:58,170
You vile woman!

491
00:28:58,610 --> 00:29:00,680
How dare you try to deceive me!

492
00:29:01,610 --> 00:29:03,610
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
